Executive summary

The 2024 Index covers XX countries in depth and YY countries in total.

Using its measurement framework, the Index brings together X individual data points from Y sources. Alongside the overall Index results, through this website you can: read articles discussing themes and countries covered in the results and interviews with those leading reform efforts, explore the data in-depth, and read the technical methodology.

Of those countries we can measure in-depth against our framework country A ranks top followed by country B and country C. Of those countries we cannot measure in-depth, country Z is the highest placed followed by country X and country Y.

Our framework analyses data about national civil services across four domains: strategy and leadership; public policy; national delivery; and, people and processes.

Read more about the overall Index results

Domain 1

Country B ranks highest for domain 1 with particular strengths in theme 1 and theme 2, while Country D comes highest in theme 3.

Read more

Domain 2

Country A ranks highest for domain 2, while Country C comes in top for theme 4.

Read more

Domain 3

Country A ranks highest for domain 3 with the highest scores for both theme 5 and theme 6.

Read more

Domain 4

Country B ranks highest for domain 4 with the highest scores for theme 7, country C ranks highest for theme 8 and country D comes top in theme 9.

Read more

Conclusions & next steps

The results provide an important tool to help countries learn from each other, however there remain crucial gaps in the availability of data to fully understand how public administrations compare.

Read our conclusions and our next steps

Making use of the results

There are many different ways you can make use of the results from the 2024 Index, read the results content, explore the data, or read articles and interviews that provide reflections on the results.

For more ideas and details on how you can make full use of the results, read our in-depth guide.
